  "preFix": {
    "title": "Coconut and red lentil soup",
    "subtitle": "Spiced, creamy, and ready in 30 minutes",
    "excerpt": "Red lentils dissolved into coconut milk and stock, spiced with turmeric, cumin, and fresh ginger. A thick, bright yellow soup that is warming without being heavy, and good enough to eat every week.",
    "sourceNotes": "Red lentil and coconut soup draws on South Indian dal traditions, particularly the tarka dal approach of blooming spices in fat and combining them with dissolved red lentils and coconut milk. Method synthesised for a British home kitchen.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Red lentils dissolve completely when cooked, thickening the soup without any blending. The spice base here follows the logic of a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "tarka",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "termId": "cmprydmpa0000ysv47akztstz"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ": cook the onion, then bloom the spices in the fat before any liquid goes in. The turmeric gives the soup its colour; the cumin and ginger give it warmth. Coconut milk goes in at the end to keep it creamy without curdling. This is a soup that can be on the table in 30 minutes.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
