        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Build the spiced base",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat {{coconut-oil}} of oil in a large saucepan over a medium heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and cook for 6 minutes until soft. Add the {{garlic}} of garlic and {{ginger-fresh}} of grated ginger and cook for 1 minute.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add {{cumin-ground}} of cumin, {{turmeric}} of turmeric, and {{chilli-flakes}} of chilli flakes. Stir for 1 minute until fragrant. Add {{tomato-puree}} of tomato purée and cook for 30 seconds.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Add lentils and simmer",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{lentils-red}} of rinsed red lentils and pour in {{stock-vegetable}} of hot stock. Bring to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the lentils have dissolved into the soup.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Stir in {{coconut-milk}} of coconut milk and the juice of {{lime}} lime. Simmer for 2 minutes. Taste and season with salt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Scatter coriander leaves over each bowl if using.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Add hot water or stock a ladleful at a time. The soup should pour easily from a ladle. When reheating from the fridge, always add water.",
                "cause": "Red lentils absorb a significant amount of liquid as they cook and thicken further on standing.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too thick"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add coconut milk after reducing the heat to a gentle simmer. Full-fat coconut milk curdles less readily than light.",
                "cause": "The coconut milk was added to a vigorously boiling soup.",
                "symptom": "Coconut milk has curdled into white specks"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Turmeric is primarily for colour. 1 tsp is enough for 200 g of lentils. Add more cumin to balance if the turmeric is prominent.",
                "cause": "Too much turmeric for the volume of lentils, or an old jar with a strong character.",
                "symptom": "Turmeric taste is strong or medicinal"
              },
              {
                "fix": "The lime juice is essential and cannot be skipped. It brightens the soup and balances the richness of the coconut milk. Taste before serving and add more lime if needed.",
                "cause": "Lime juice and salt were not added at the end.",
                "symptom": "Flavour is flat"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Red lentil soups spiced with cumin, turmeric, and ginger are found across South Asia, the Middle East, and Sri Lanka. The coconut milk element comes from South Indian and Sri Lankan cooking, where coconut milk is used in both dal and soups. This version became widely popular in Britain in the 2000s as coconut milk moved from specialist shops to every supermarket shelf.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
